  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n**Without having changed the test script nor the contracts**, the integration test fails at the beforeEach step that deploys the ERC20 contract.\r\n\r\nThe shorthand of the error log is below:\r\n```\r\nError: transaction failed\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe error code is `CALL_EXCEPTION`.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. `git clone https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism-tutorial.git`\r\n2. Install deps: `yarn`\r\n3. Compile ERC20 contract: `yarn hardhat compile --network optimism`\r\n4. Run tests and see error: `yarn hardhat test --network optimism`\r\n\r\nThe truncated error log is below, truncating tx data:\r\n<img width=\"926\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-05-10 at 1 58 28 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37757724/117710500-ccdac700-b197-11eb-99d5-8450e8f8d3c7.png\">\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nTests should pass, since no logic was changed in the repository except for hardcoding `gasPrice: 0` and `gasLimit: 8999999` to contract calls. \r\nWithout hardcoding `gasLimit: 8999999` to the call to deploy the contract in the integration test, I receive the `UNPREDICTABLE_GAS_LIMIT` error.\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nTests were made against `v0.3.0-rc` of the optimism/ops tool.",
